Totally guessing here since I don't know how much you've changed from vmangos and what @jameyboor did for https://github.com/slowtorta/turtlewow-bug-tracker/issues/374 but would love to see this fixed:

Perhaps a call to `Aura::Update` was added before the `bool reapplyIgnite = igniteAura->GetAuraTicks() >= igniteAura->GetAuraMaxTicks();` check in `HandleDummyAuraProc` to make sure damage was happening before ignite refresh?  Don't think it fully explains the 3 ticks when there is no ignite aura yet but would explain the refresh window going from 4s -> 2s

Other thing I noticed was this boolean is confusing as it is getting inverted 
```
bool reapplyIgnite = igniteAura->GetAuraTicks() >= igniteAura->GetAuraMaxTicks();
if (!reapplyIgnite)
{
    ...
    // Refresh Ignite Stack
    igniteHolder->Refresh(igniteAura->GetCaster(), target, igniteHolder);
}
```
makes me wonder if that led to a mistake

@luskanek the idol at that point and time did reduce Savage Bite's cost by 3, and this bug did appear. 
![image](https://github.com/slowtorta/turtlewow-bug-tracker/assets/151180101/f6a11de7-9a14-4d31-b2b7-ebf76d447343)
The idol is back to its 1.12 version, and so this bug has been fixed.

@cyaohiri @twowTurtReynolds  I can confirm the same on the Warlock as the mage.

I guess now I have more questions as to why it worked before and now. What has changed?

Last question, can it be modified to allow it work without the GCD? Can the cooldowns be different?

